FBIS3-51705 "drlat016_o_94004" FBIS-LAT-94-016 Document Type:Daily Report 26 Jan 1994 Colombia Church, Bottling Plant Bombed To Protest U.S. Troops PA2501014494 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 1 in Spanish 0000 GMT 25 Jan 94 PA2501014494 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 1 Language: Spanish Article Type:BFN [Report over video by Janeth Cepeda from Bucaramanga; from the "24 Hours" newscast] [Text] According to an investigation by the intelligence division of the Santander Police Department, two medium-power explosive devices were detonated in a Mormon church and a soft drink bottling plant in Bucaramanga to protest the presence of U.S. soldiers in Colombia. [Begin recording of Santander Police Commander Colonel Hugo Lozano, identified by caption] These explosive devices were placed by the Army of National Liberation to protest the presence of U.S. Marines in Colombian territory. [end recording] The explosive devices, which contained 2 kg of dynamite apiece, were detonated at the same time. In the Mormon church, the damage was estimated at 7 million pesos. Seven years ago, another attack completely destroyed the church.
